snippet.textDisplay:
I bought a fake 1050 about a year ago. I don't remember the details, but the actual card was not that bad value for the price. I reported it fake, and got the money back, so in the end I got a usable card for free. But there was a huge issue with it. The card reported that it had 2GB of VRAM, but in reality it only got 1GB. So every time a game wanted to load anything above 1GB, it just froze. Very few games was usable this way, but it did run Borderlands 2 more or less fine. After some trial and error I managed to hack back a firmware that was compatible enough with it. It works now, but only 1 connector out of 3. If I tried other firmwares I probably could made at least one more connector work.
I don't use it anymore, I bought a used GTX 960. If anyone wants to play with it I can send you for postal fee (in the EU).
